InnovationCrisis Leadership: Using Technology To Maintain Stability And GrowthByPhil Portman,Forbes Councils Member.for Forbes Technology CouncilCOUNCIL POSTExpertise from Forbes Councils members, operated under license. Opinions expressed are those of the author. | Membership (fee-based)Jul 09, 2024, 08:30am EDTPhil Portman is a serial entrepreneur and the Founder & CEO of Textdrip — a small business SMS marketing tool to automate SMS campaigns. gettyWhen things are going well, leadership looks like an easy task. Right? The economy is growing, people's incomes are increasing and your organization is getting more orders.In short, all is well. So you don't need to make quick decisions.You can easily plan for the quarter, set your goals and be a true visionary leader for your colleagues, society and investors. However, the real leadership challenge arises during the crisis. Using cutting-edge technologies, you can easily survive these VUCAP times.VUCAP is an acronym where each character signifies a specific crisis condition.• V: Volatility.• U: Uncertainty.• C: Complexity.• A: Ambiguity.• P: Pandemic.The best way to deal with VUCAP times is to use automated communication tools. These tools can improve and integrate workflow management, collaboration, strategic planning and AI automation for organizational resilience.Crisis Leadership: The Cornerstone Of StabilityCrisis leadership means enabling the organization to adapt to any unexpected event and try to ease its effects by protecting the stakeholder's trust and organizational stability. if (!window.cnxel) { window.cnxel = {}; window.cnxel.cmd = []; var iframe = document.createElement('iframe'); iframe.style.display = 'none'; iframe.onload = function() { var iframeDoc = iframe.contentWindow.document; var script = iframeDoc.createElement('script'); script.src = '//cd.elements.video/player.js?cid=62cec241-7d09-4462-afc2-f72f8d8ef40a'; script.setAttribute('defer', '1'); script.setAttribute('type', 'text/javascript'); iframeDoc.body.appendChild(script); }; document.head.appendChild(iframe); const preloadResourcesEndpoint = 'https://cds.elements.video/a/preload-resources-ovp.json'; fetch(preloadResourcesEndpoint, { priority: 'low' }) .then(response => { if (!response.ok) { throw new Error('Network response was not ok', preloadResourcesEndpoint); } return response.json(); }) .then(data => { const cssUrl = data.css; const cssUrlLink = document.createElement('link'); cssUrlLink.rel = 'stylesheet'; cssUrlLink.href = cssUrl; cssUrlLink.as = 'style'; cssUrlLink.media = 'print'; cssUrlLink.onload = function() { this.media = 'all'; }; document.head.appendChild(cssUrlLink); const hls = data.hls; const hlsScript = document.createElement('script'); hlsScript.src = hls; hlsScript.setAttribute('defer', '1'); hlsScript.setAttribute('type', 'text/javascript'); document.head.appendChild(hlsScript); }).catch(error => { console.error('There was a problem with the fetch operation:', error); }); } These crises can be natural disasters, financial recessions or technological failures. Identifying these crises in their early stages can help organizations develop strategies to mitigate their negative impact.Effective crisis leadership can ensure long-term success and stability.As an effective crisis leader, you must possess the following qualities.1. DecisivenessAs a leader, you must be able to move your organization forward, even with any conflicting, confusing or changing information. Decisiveness does not mean rigidity. You must be able to quickly decide what to do even though the situation awareness keeps evolving. 2. EmpathyWhen leaders are empathetic, they can help their teams become stronger, even in adverse situations. So, understand the emotional impact of a crisis before making any decision. 3. TransparencyYou must remain transparent in communication and leadership. It can improve credibility, strengthen relationships with stakeholders and mitigate the adverse effects on your organization's reputation.4. AdaptabilityAs a leader during a crisis, you cannot remain married to one strategy. You need to constantly consider new information, consult with people who understand what is happening, listen carefully and be willing to adapt to it.The Pivotal Role Of Technology In Crisis ManagementKey technology tools facilitate seamless communication and operational resilience. Emerging technologies like drones, AI, social media, big data and data analytics can help crisis management leaders better understand, respond to and recuperate from crises.The main aim of these tools is to bring all the required activities for planning and dealing with the crisis in one place.Google Alerts, Factal, Everbridge and Brandwatch are a few crisis management tools that support organizations during the crisis for effective communication, automating workflows and making informed decisions.Strategic Use Of Automated Communication ToolsAutomated communication tools can help organizations thrive. They simplify internal and external communication, work allocation and project management and improve efficiency by delivering a personalized experience. 1. Automated SMS And Email AlertsSuppose you want timely and consistent communication. You can use automated SMS and email marketing platforms to send automated SMS and email alerts and expect quick responses. First, choose the right platform, register your number, choose the plan and template and set up keywords. Then, automated SMS or email alerts will be sent to the concerned person whenever you receive the keyword.2. Chatbots For Enhanced Customer SupportDuring a crisis, you can experience surges in consumer inquiries. To provide timely customer support, use AI-driven chatbots. They can improve the consumer experience, personalization, process automation and minimize consumer support costs, so your organization can experience optimal performance.3. Virtual Collaboration PlatformsTools like Slack and Microsoft Teams support remote work. As per one study, more than 75% of professionals use such tools. They have features like integrated chat, video conferencing, file sharing and task management to help maximize team productivity.4. Video Conferencing SolutionsEffective video conferencing can help the team remain on the same page. You can conduct high-quality virtual meetings from anywhere using Zoom and Google Meet. You can also conduct webinars for knowledge-sharing sessions with your team.5. Project Management SoftwareProject management tools like Trello and Asana offer flexibility in organizing tasks, projects and ideas. They can streamline workflows. These tools are simple to use and improve digital collaboration through visual boards.6. Social Media And PR AutomationSocial media and PR automation tools help manage public relations and crisis communications. You can use them to develop an effective social media management strategy. For example, you can set clear guidelines to monitor social media platforms and deal with negative comments.Crisis Management Practices To Build A Resilient OrganizationThe following are a few more strategies you can implement in order to build resiliency in your business.• As a crisis leader, you must first research organizational needs and resource evaluation. Based on this, you must allocate resources.• Make a dedicated crisis management team with relevant proficiency and decision making authority. • Conduct risk assessment and find out potential risks and vulnerabilities and their impact. • Create a detailed plan to respond to the crisis, including roles, communication protocols, responsibilities, etc.• Establish effective communication channels for smooth communication, so information flow remains the same internally and externally.• You should train your crisis team regularly and conduct mock drills to test how effective your crisis management plan is and whether any improvement is required.• Integrate the right technological tools to enable smooth communication, work allocation and tracking. This can that your crisis response plan is executed correctly.ConclusionYou can transform the landscape of crisis management through proactive and adaptive leadership. To drive stability and enjoy increased ROI, you should learn how to harness technological power. You can use different automated communication tools to increase operational capabilities to withstand, adapt and recover from unexpected events.So, depending on your business requirements, scale and the nature of the crisis, you should select tools that make things accessible and functional for each team member. Use technological innovation optimally to give your business an edge over risks and make it future-proof against crisis.Forbes Technology Council is an invitation-only community for world-class CIOs, CTOs and technology executives. Do I qualify?Editorial StandardsReprints & PermissionsLOADING VIDEO PLAYER...FORBES' FEATURED Video
